  <summary date="2017-03-17T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Wounded Veterans Recreation Act

This bill amends the Federal Lands Recreation Enhancement Act to require the National Parks and Federal Recreational Lands Pass, which is made available for the lifetime of the passholder without charge to any U.S. citizen or person domiciled in the United States who has been medically determined to be permanently disabled, to be made available to any veteran with a service-connected disability.</summary>
